notesStmt.note: Opening rubric: Cera specialissima contra maleficia (p. 1).

msContents.summary: Prayers (including several litanies) and exorcisms in Latin, with some recipes in German. Table of contents added by a later hand at the beginning of the volume.

msItem.title: Cerae, fumigia, pulvera, benedictiones et exorcismi contra malificia

supportDesc.extent: 112 leaves : 178 x 107 (152 x 91) mm. bound to 182 x 108 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 112 leaves; [iv], 1-130, 132-140, [ii], 141-154, [ii], 155-180, 189-192, [ii], 193-203, 203-229, [iii]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper center.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand, with two folios added in the front in a second, slightly later hand.

binding.p: Contemporary parchment (leaf from an earlier missal). Some oxidation of ink.

origin.p: Written in Germany in the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Possible ownership inscription: Dreisch (f. i recto).

keywords.term: Catholic Church--Prayers and devotions--Early works to 1800
